e:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. memoQ is best suited for professional translators, LSPs, translation agencies, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Smartling, meanwhile, shines for enterprise localization, SaaS companies, global brands, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2004, memoQ describes itself as \"Professional CAT tool and translation management system for linguists.\" Smartling, established in 2009, positions itself as \"Enterprise translation management platform combining AI and human translation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
f:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Smartling** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 8). However, this does not mean memoQ is a poor choice — far from it. memoQ excels in its own right, particularly for professional translators and LSPs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent enterprise tms platform, go with Smartling. If powerful professional cat tool matters more to you, memoQ is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
